      "id": "note_1",
      "text": "AM I A NIGHT OWL? — NZ Yr 9–13\n\nHidden truth: this is an EVENING type (owl) — activity peaks at about 22:00 and rest is in the early hours. Frame the biology around homeostasis/feedback, with the body clock (circadian rhythm) as the worked example.\n\nCurriculum (NZ): NZC Living World — Life processes (L7/8); NCEA AS91604 (homeostasis). Intl: AP Bio 8.1, IB Bio D3.3.\nNCEA is transitional: L1 removed from 2028; NZCE (Yr12) 2029; NZACE (Yr13) 2030. Standards below remain valid through the change.\n\nFull mapping + worked walkthrough: classroom-handbook.html",
